an ode to home. 

i spent the last three months making a house a home. it was important for me to create a space; to build this life with @kobrakawaii_gabriel and it was hard. I worked non-stop. i didn’t need to but i wanted to because I was closing a chapter. i was stepping away from a city that helped me grow into the person i am today; a place that i knew every corner off since stepping foot on its concrete sidewalks at eighteen; i was putting distance between friendships that existed decades plus and new ones that helped me laugh. i am taking a leap and truthfully, even though i still maybe moving on adrenaline it’s time for the dust to settle, but let me tell you i worked too damn hard for this piece of paradise and i ‘m proud of myself (my bank account not so much). i deserve to look back at it and give myself props. i sacrificed a summer, many sleepless nights; lots of tears (and almost quit) but I’m here because i believe in me and i want this…so here it is thus far… hope to continue to enjoy this new chapter. happy moving day.

Cheers to another year of leveling up my brilliant, @kobrakawaii_gabriel ! 🎉📚 So happy to spend another birthday with you and although we are getting older, the adventures are just beginning! Stop driving me crazy and let’s laugh our way through this life together. Always here to support your ventures! Love your biggest cheerleader! Happy birthday, Gabe! 🎂💫 #BirthdayVibes"
